This 36-inch Voodoo Tactical brand padded rifle carrying case will help protect your rifle from the hard knocks of transportation, whether in your vehicle or in the field. It can also be used if you break down your gun or to carry different uppers.

Inside are two sets of adjustable tie downs so that you can be sure your optics are not going to get knocked about. Behind the pouches, there's a second compartment with two padded pouches built in. Each is designed to hold a pistol, but you could also use these for optics or other accessories.
This case comes with the three external pouches you see here, giving you plenty of storage space for magazines, boxes of ammo, cleaning kits, your log book and other accessories. The three exterior pouches have gussets, making them hold far more than you would think. The two outside pouches can hold five or six standard size magazines and the center pouch is even larger.

This Voodoo Tactical gun case features three carrying methods: A standard handle in center of the bag, a shoulder strap, and back-pack style shoulder harness. This backpack style carry is great for long distances. And if you use the PAL webbing to attach MOLLE or ALICE pouches, you can haul even more gear.

These bags are top notch and will last last a life time!

title: For Sale/Trade:  Big Game Rifle. And I mean BIG.
postcontent:
Ruger No. 1 in .458 Win Mag.
According to the Ruger handbook, a rare and collectable combination of sights, and caliber.
It does have some wear from the previous owner, but is still in about 98% quality. Only scratches in the wood are just in the finish. Blue-ing is beautiful.

I have the Ruger custom scope rings, if you prefer taking your game at a distance, leather sling, recoil absorber, hard case, and a 9 round sleeve, for quick follow up shots. Though I doubt you'd need one, while firing one of the 19 500gr, 5,000+ft/lbs rounds that I have.

The round puts out over 4/3 as much power as the 7mm Magnum, and is good for any game that walks this Earth. 
For hunting, you can take any game you please, as long as you have the permit.
 For home defense, it is a heavy gun, to absorb the recoil, but single shot weapons are 4 inches shorter than respective lever or bolt guns, due to not needing the action, making it shorter than an 870 shotgun. And the .458 round can shatter an elephant skull. I'm sure that it can make short work of any armor any intruder will wear.
Worried about zombies? I'm sure this will make chunky salsa out of a line of them.
Plinking? Honestly, no. At $100+ for a box of 20, you better be rich if you plan on taking this to the range every weekend. But if you reload? From what I've read, .45 "Long" Colt rounds will work, allowing you to shoot for much cheaper, if you're not worried about Dangerous Game.

Single action sucks? A skilled operator can use this rig just as fast as a bolt action rifle.
Also, if you see a man taking a single shot rifle out of the case, and on a hunt, it says something about him. The silence of any onlookers tells you that they know you're both a more skilled hunter, and a better marksman than any of them.

title: For Sale/Trade:  SURPLUS RUSSIAN SVT-40 1941 7.62X54 SEMI AUTO RIFLE SVT40 10rd mag
postcontent:
Back up for sale due to buyers funds fell through. Prefer local sale in SC only for cash , otherwise only ship to FFL Dealer. Very rare hard to find (1941) RUSSIAN SVT-40 RIFLE - 7.62x54r caliber semi-automatic rifle. 10 round detachable magazine. The Samozaryadnaya Vintovka Tokareva (SVT-40) was designed by Soviet Arms Designer Fedor Tokarev. It was manufactured between 1941 and 1945. The SVT-40 is an improved and simplified rifle design over the SVT-38. During WWII SVT-40 rifles were highly prized captures by both German and Finnish troops. Many pictures in books of German troops on the eastern front carrying the SVT-40. The biggest issue with the SVT 40 is the ejection of the spent casing due to improper gas cartridge adjustment and improper powder loads. DO NOT use any loads over 150 grain as this will destroy the gas chamber. Overall condition is rated as fair to good for an old surplus military rifle that will never be imported again into the USA. 10 magazine is an aftermarket, so not all original, all other numbers match THAT I CAN TELL. Wood stock has 3 cracks/splits at rear top of receiver and at bottom of mag well. Gun has some surface rust spots. I would grade gun and bore as fair to good condition. title: For Sale:  22 Mag Ranger-Ser. # NRAWLF1
postcontent:
This handsome .22 Magnum Ranger is one of the last  examples of an experimental production run by North American Arms. The decision was made not to enter full-scale production and this is one of the few examples of this special gun that will ever be available.



One other example of this rare firearm auctioned for more than $3,200 on GunBroker.com.



Following a test production of 500 guns in 2011, North American Arms reluctantly decided to end production because the hand assembly required to achieve the high quality that NAA demanded proved just too expensive.



  Since North American Arms announced that they would cease production, the Rangers have been soaring in value. One Ranger recently auctioned for more than $3,200.00 on GunBroker.com. All proceeds from this auction will benefit the NRA Women's Leadership Forum.



This one-of-a-kind Ladies Leadership Forum offering features special serial # NRAWLF1. Gun comes in a custom presentation case provided by North American Arms.


   Thanks to North American Arms for this generous donation.
